tor%20General%20of%20Police%20(DIG)%20Ali%20Mohammad%20Watali%2C%20in%20Raj%20Bagh%20residential%20area%20of%20Srinagar%20city.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EOne%20terrorist%20identified%20as%20Aijaz%20Dar%2C%20who%20lived%20in%20the%20nearby%20Jawahar%20Nagar%20area%2C%20was%20killed%20in%20retaliatory%20firing%20by%20the%20guards%20at%20the%20DIG's%20house%20and%20one%20assault%20rifle%20was%20recovered%20from%20him.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EAnother%20senior%20police%20officer%2C%20Shaikh%20Owais%2C%20was%20the%20Superintendent%20of%20Police%20(SP)%2C%20Srinagar%20at%20that%20time.%20Owais%20was%20among%20the%20first%20senior%20officers%20to%20reach%20the%20DIG's%20residence%20since%20he%20also%20lived%20in%20the%20same%20area.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThis%20was%20a%20weapon%20not%20in%20use%20in%20the%20police%20force%2C%20nor%20was%20it%20the%20standard%20weapon%20issued%20to%20the%20army%20back%20then.%20At%20a%20meeting%20of%20the%20experts%20called%20in%20from%20the%20army%2C%20the%20weapon%20was%20identified%20as%20a%20Kalashnikov.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EIt%20belonged%20to%20a%20family%20of%20assault%20rifles%20also%20known%20as%20AK%20platform%2C%20AK%20rifle%20or%20simply%20AK%20based%20on%20the%20original%20design%20of%20Mikhail%20Kalashnikov.%20Experts%20identified%20the%20rifle%20as%20AK-47%2C%20officially%20known%20as%20the%20Avtomat%20Kalashnikova%20which%20is%20the%20originating%20firearm%20of%20the%20Kalashnikov%20family%20of%20rifles.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EIt%20was%20developed%20in%20the%20Soviet%20Union%20by%20Russian%20small-arms%20designer%20Mikhail%20Kalashnikov%20in%20the%20middle%20of%20the%2020th%20century.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BAK-47's%20name%20stands%20for%20Automat%20Kalashnikova%201947%2C%20the%20year%20it%20was%20first%20produced.%20In%201949%2C%20the%20AK-47%20became%20the%20assault%20rifle%20of%20the%20Soviet%20Army%2C%26quot%3B%20an%20officer%20said.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EOver%20the%20years%2C%20since%201988%2C%20the%20terrorists%20started%20using%20long-range%20sniper%20rifles%20and%20also%20the%20subsequent%20versions%20of%20the%20AK%20rifle%20series%20like%20AK-54%20and%20AK-74%20denoting%20the%20year%20of%20manufacture%20of%20the%20rifle%20with%20improvements%20over%20the%20original%20AK-47%20version.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20Jammu%20and%20Kashmir%20police%20force%20was%20not%20issued%20any%20assault%20rifle%20of%20the%20AK%20series%20till%20then%2C%20and%20to%20combat%20the%20firepower%20of%20the%20adversary%2C%20police%2C%20paramilitary%20and%20the%20army%20were%20subsequently%20issued%20assault%20rifles%20of%20the%20AK%20series%20as%20well%20in%20addition%20to%20Indian-made%20INSAS%20rifles.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BThe%20possession%20of%20AK%20assault%20rifles%20by%20the%20terrorists%20unequivocally%20established%20that%20they%20had%20been%20trained%20and%20issued%20weapons%20by%20trainers%20of%20the%20Pakistan%20army.%20Due%20to%20the%20presence%20of%20the%20Russians%20in%20Afghanistan%20and%20Pakistan's%20support%20to%20the%20Afghan%20militias%2C%20AK%20rifles%20were%20aplenty%20in%20Pakistan%20since%20practically%20no%20border%20existed%20between%20the%20two%20countries%20at%20that%20time%2C%26quot%3B%20said%20a%20senior%20intelligence%20officer.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EAs%20terrorism%20intensified%20due%20to%20the%20entry%20of%20foreign%20mercenaries%20into%20Jammu%20and%20Kashmir%20by%20the%20middle%20of%201990s%2C%20more%20weapons%20in%20their%20improvised%20versions%20like%20AK-54%2C%20AK-74%20and%20under-barrel%20grenade%20launchers%20(UBGLs)%20came%20to%20be%20used%20by%20the%20terrorists.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3ESince%20the%20foreign%20mercenaries%20were%20battle-hardened%2C%20the%20security%20forces%20had%20to%20live%20up%20to%20the%20growing%20challenge%20by%20introducing%20the%20Para%20commandos%20and%20those%20trained%20in%20mountain%20warfare%20into%20its%20anti-terrorism%20operations%20in%20Jammu%20and%20Kashmir.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BJ%26amp%3BK%20police%20also%20underwent%20a%20sweeping%20change%20in%20its%20training%20of%20commandos%2C%20use%20and%20expertise%20of%20modern%20assault%20rifles%20and%20strenuous%20training%20in%20developing%20stamina%20and%20focus.%20Commitment%20to%20eradicate%20terrorism%20and%20usher%20in%20peace%20was%20the%20preamble%20of%20such%20training%2C%26quot%3B%20said%20a%20senior%20police%20officer%20supervising%20physical%20and%20weapon%20handling%20training%20of%20the%20local%20police%20force.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EParamilitary%20forces%20like%20BSF%20and%20CRPF%20were%20not%20behind%20in%20bringing%20their%20troops%20up%20to%20the%20maximum%20level%20of%20efficiency%20to%20deal%20with%20terrorism%20in%20different%20parts%20of%20the%20country.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EAs%20terrorism%20started%20getting%20more%20hands%20by%20way%20of%20foreign%20mercenaries%20who%20were%20pushed%20into%20Jammu%20and%20Kashmir%20from%20across%20the%20border%2C%20motivated%20and%20indoctrinated%20by%20both%20religious%20fanaticism%20and%20the%20lure%20of%20money%2C%20the%20handlers%20and%20their%20masters%20in%20the%20Pakistan%20army%20started%20encouraging%20them%20with%20better%20weapons.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EOn%20July%2011%2C%202022%2C%20one%20M4%20carbine%20rifle%20was%20recovered%20from%20an%20encounter%20site%20in%20the%20Awantipora%20area%20of%20Jammu%20and%20Kashmir's%20Pulwama%20district%20where%20Jaish-e-Muhammad%20commander%2C%20Kaiser%20Koka%20and%20another%20terrorist%20were%20killed.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThis%20was%20a%20new%20challenge%20for%20the%20security%20forces.%20The%20M4%20carbine%20also%20replaced%20most%20submachine%20guns%20and%20selected%20handguns%20in%20US%20military%20service%2C%20as%20it%20fired%20more%20effective%20rifle%20ammunition%20that%20offered%20superior%20stopping%20power%20and%20was%20better%20able%20to%20penetrate%20modern%20body%20armour.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BA%20review%20had%20become%20necessary%20of%20the%20bulletproof%20vests%20issued%20to%20the%20security%20forces.%20The%20older%20version%20of%20the%20bullet%20proof%20jacket%20wouldn't%20suffice%20to%20meet%20the%20new%20challenge.%20Better%20and%20lighter%20BP%20jackets%20have%20been%20issued%20to%20security%20forces%20fighting%20terrorism%20and%20these%20are%20designed%20to%20stop%20the%20armour-piercing%20bullets%2C%26quot%3B%20said%20another%20senior%20police%20officer%20deployed%20on%20anti-terrorism%20operations.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EWhile%20the%20M4%20assault%20rifle%20is%20US-made%20and%20it%20is%20issued%20to%20the%20American%20army%2C%20it%20is%20obvious%20that%20while%20leaving%20Afghanistan%2C%20the%20US%20forces%20left%20behind%20some%20of%20their%20sophisticated%20weaponry%20which%20came%20into%20the%20hands%20of%20the%20Afghan%20fighters.%20This%20assault%20rifle%20found%20its%20way%20into%20Jammu%20and%20Kashmir%20through%20Pakistan.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EOn%20July%2017%2C%202024%2C%20two%20foreign%20terrorists%20were%20killed%20by%20the%20army%20while%20foiling%20an%20infiltration%20bid%20on%20the%20Line%20of%20Control%20in%20the%20Keran%20sector.%20A%20Steyr%20AUG%20assault%20rifle%20was%20recovered%20from%20the%20slain%20terrorists.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20StG%2077%20(Sturmgewehr%2077)%20is%20the%20designation%20given%20by%20the%20Austrian%20Armed%20Forces%20when%20they%20adopted%20the%20Steyr%20AUG%20in%201977.%20This%20is%20the%20standard%20assault%20rifle%20issued%20to%20the%20Austrian%20army.%20The%20Steyr%20bullpup%20assault%20rifle%20is%20only%20matched%20by%20the%20Israeli-made%20Tavor%20assault%20rifle.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3ETavor%20is%20a%20gas-operated%2C%20selective-fire%20bullpup%20assault%20rifle%20built%20around%20a%20long-stroke%20piston%20system.%20The%20main%20objective%20behind%20the%20development%20of%20Tavor%20is%20to%20maximise%20reliability%2C%20durability%2C%20simplicity%20of%20design%2C%20and%20maintenance-free%2C%20particularly%20under%20unfavourable%20or%20battlefield%20conditions.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BTavor%20has%20a%20semi-automatic%20mode%2C%20burst%20mode%20and%20full-auto%20mode%20chambered%20in%20standard%205.56x45%20mm%20ammunition.%20It%20is%20considered%20to%20be%20more%20reliable%20and%20accurate%20than%20the%20M4%20carbine%20of%20the%20US%20and%20Steyr%20of%20Austria.%20The%20Tavor%20TAR-21%20holds%20magazines%20of%2030%20rounds%2C%26quot%3B%20said%20an%20arms%20expert.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EAs%20challenges%20are%20in%20plenty%20for%20the%20security%20forces%20fighting%20terrorism%20in%20J%26amp%3BK%2C%20weapons%20systems%2C%20armour-resistant%20apparel%20and%20other%20equipment%20used%20by%20our%20security%20forces%20are%20regularly%20and%20constantly%20reviewed.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BA%20couple%20of%20M4%20carbine%20rifles%20or%20Austrian%20bullpup%20assault%20rifles%20cannot%20save%20the%20terrorist%20from%20a%20professionally%20trained%20and%20highly%20modernised%20army%20of%20India%2C%26quot%3B%20said%20the%20senior%20intelligence%20officer.%3C%2Fp%3E%22%2C%22published%22%3A1721471460000%2C%22visual%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fc.ndtvimg.com%2F2024-07%2Fvn25in6g_steyr_625x300_20_July_24.jpeg%22%2C%22originID%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.ndtv.com%2Findia-news%2Fwhat-recovery-of-austrian-assault-rifle-from-j-k-terrorists-means-6146713%22%2C%22summary%22%3A%22The%20recovery%20of%20an%20Austrian%20assault%20rifle%20from%20two%20slain%20foreign%20terrorists%20in%20Jammu%20and%20Kashmir's%20Keran%20sector%20on%20July%2018%20has%20added%20another%20complex%20dimension%20to%20the%20ongoing%20terrorism%20in%20the%20Union%20Territory.%22%2C%22author%22%3A%22%22%2C%22engagement%22%3A3%2C%22canonicalUrl%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.ndtv.com%2Findia-news%2Fwhat-recovery-of-austrian-assault-rifle-from-j-k-terrorists-means-6146713%22%2C%22cdnAmpUrl%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww-ndtv-com.cdn.ampproject.org%2Fc%2Fs%2Fwww.ndtv.com%2Findia-news%2Fwhat-recovery-of-austrian-assault-rifle-from-j-k-terrorists-means-6146713%2Famp%2F1%22%2C%22ampUrl%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.ndtv.com%2Findia-news%2Fwhat-recovery-of-austrian-assault-rifle-from-j-k-terrorists-means-6146713%2Famp%2F1%22%7D%2C%7B%22title%22%3A%22Bangladesh%20unrest%3A%20Nearly%201000%20Indian%20students%20back%20home%2C%20says%20MEA%22%2C%22content%22%3A%22%22%2C%22published%22%3A1721470124000%2C%22visual%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fstatic.toiimg.com%2Fphoto%2Fmsid-111883839%2Cimgsize-1685547.cms%22%2C%22originID%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Ftimesofindia.indiatimes.com%2Findia%2Fbangladesh-unrest-nearly-1000-indian-students-back-home-mea-says-repatriation-efforts-ongoing%2Farticleshow%2F111883517.cms%22%2C%22summary%22%3A%22%22%2C%22author%22%3A%22TOI%20NEWS%20DESK%22%2C%22engagement%22%3A0%2C%22canonicalUrl%22%3A%22%22%2C%22cdnAmpUrl%22%3A%22%22%2C%22ampUrl%22%3A%22%22%7D%2C%7B%22title%22%3A%22Nearly%201%2C000%20Indian%20Students%20Return%20From%20Bangladesh%2C%204%2C000%20Still%20Remain%22%2C%22content%22%3A%22%3Cp%3EAs%20the%20civil%20unrest%20in%20Bangladesh%20continues%2C%20the%20Indian%20High%20Commission%20in%20Dhaka%20is%20facilitating%20safe%20travel%20for%20Indian%20students%20to%20crossing%20points%20along%20the%20India-Bangladesh%20International%20Border.%20The%20Ministry%20of%20External%20Affairs%20(MEA)%20is%20also%20collaborating%20with%20civil%20aviation%2C%20immigration%2C%20land%20ports%2C%20and%20the%20Border%20Security%20Force%20(BSF)%20to%20ensure%20a%20smooth%20passage%20for%20Indian%20nationals.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3ESo%20far%2C%20778%20Indian%20students%20have%20successfully%20returned%20to%20India%20via%20various%20land%20ports.%20Additionally%2C%20around%20200%20students%20have%20returned%20home%20by%20regular%20flight%20services%20through%20Dhaka%20and%20Chittagong%20airports%2C%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.mea.gov.in%2Fpress-releases.htm%3Fdtl%2F37982%2FUpdate_on_Return_of_Indian_Nationals_in_Bangladesh%5C%22%3Ethe%20MEA%20said%20in%20a%20statement%3C%2Fa%3E.%20The%20High%20Commission%20is%20in%20regular%20contact%20with%20more%20than%204%2C000%20students%20still%20in%20various%20universities%20across%20Bangladesh.%20Students%20from%20Nepal%20and%20Bhutan%20have%20also%20been%20aided%20in%20crossing%20into%20India%20upon%20request.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BMany%20students%20had%20booked%20air%20tickets.%20But%20since%20there%20is%20a%20curfew%20in%20place%2C%20they%20could%20not%20make%20it%20to%20the%20airport.%20Several%20flights%20were%20also%20cancelled.%20There%20are%20still%20many%20Indian%20students%20still%20in%20hostels%20at%20universities%20where%20the%20atmosphere%20is%20still%20peaceful%2C%26quot%3B%20an%20Indian%20student%20who%20returned%20from%20Bangladesh%20told%20NDTV.%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20High%20Commission%20in%20Dhaka%20is%20also%20coordinating%20with%20Bangladesh's%20civil%20aviation%20authorities%20and%20commercial%20airlines%20to%20ensure%20uninterrupted%20flight%20services%20to%20India%20from%20Dhaka%20and%20Chittagong%2C%20which%20can%20be%20used%20by%20Indian%20nationals%20to%20return%20home.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Ch3%3E%3Cstrong%3EWhat's%20Happening%20In%20Bangladesh%3F%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fh3%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EBangladesh%20has%20plunged%20into%20turmoil%20this%20week%20as%20clashes%20between%20student%20protesters%2C%20security%20officials%2C%20and%20pro-government%20student%20activists%20erupted%20over%20a%20contentious%20quota%20system%20for%20government%20jobs.%20The%20escalating%20violence%20has%20prompted%20protest%20organizers%20to%20call%20for%20a%20nationwide%20shutdown%2C%20with%20universities%20across%20the%20country%20closing%20their%20doors%20indefinitely%20in%20response%20to%20the%20unrest.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cdiv%3E%5Cn%3Cdiv%3E%3Cimg%20alt%3D%5C%22Latest%20and%20Breaking%20News%20on%20NDTV%5C%22%20title%3D%5C%22Latest%20and%20Breaking%20News%20on%20NDTV%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fc.ndtvimg.com%2F2024-07%2Fg3hoga28_bangladesh-protests-reuters-_625x300_20_July_24.jpg%5C%22%3E%3C%2Fdiv%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EPhoto%20Credit%3A%20Reuters%20%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3C%2Fdiv%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20protests%2C%20which%20began%20late%20last%20month%2C%20reached%20a%20boiling%20point%20on%20Monday%20when%20student%20activists%20at%20Dhaka%20University%2C%20the%20largest%20university%20in%20the%20country%2C%20engaged%20in%20violent%20clashes%20with%20police%20and%20counter-protesters%20aligned%20with%20the%20ruling%20Awami%20League.%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20quota%20reserves%20up%20to%2030%20per%20cent%20of%20government%20jobs%20for%20family%20members%20of%20veterans%20who%20fought%20in%20Bangladesh's%201971%20war%20of%20independence%20against%20Pakistan.%20Protesters%20argue%20that%20this%20system%20is%20discriminatory%20and%20disproportionately%20benefits%20supporters%20of%20Prime%20Minister%20Sheikh%20Hasina's%20Awami%20League%20party.%20They%20advocate%20for%20a%20merit-based%20system%20to%20replace%20the%20existing%20quota.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Ch3%3E%3Cstrong%3EProtests%20Intensify%C2%A0%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fh3%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20situation%20in%20the%20country%20has%20escalated%2C%20with%20soldiers%20patrolling%20cities%20to%20quell%20the%20civil%20unrest.%20Riot%20police%20have%20fired%20on%20protesters%20who%20defied%20a%20government-imposed%20curfew%2C%20leading%20to%20a%20volatile%20and%20dangerous%20environment.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThis%20week's%20violence%20has%20resulted%20in%20at%20least%20115%20deaths%2C%20posing%20a%20monumental%20challenge%20to%20PM%20Hasina's%20government.%20The%20curfew%2C%20which%20went%20into%20effect%20at%20midnight%2C%20was%20accompanied%20by%20a%20request%20from%20the%20PM%20Hasina's%20office%20for%20military%20deployment%20after%20police%20failed%20to%20subdue%20widespread%20disorder.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BThe%20army%20has%20been%20deployed%20nationwide%20to%20control%20the%20law%20and%20order%20situation%2C%26quot%3B%20Bangladesh%20armed%20forces%20spokesperson%20Shahdat%20Hossain%20told%20news%20agency%20AFP.%20The%20curfew%20will%20remain%20in%20effect%20until%20at%20least%2010%3A00%20am%20on%20Sunday%2C%20according%20to%20local%20medi