se%20%3Cem%3Echana%20%3C%2Fem%3Eand%20rajma%20soaked%20overnight.%20One%20of%20the%20cons%20of%20this%20system%20is%20that%20we%20cannot%20make%20chapatis%20and%20add%20tadka%20to%20the%20%3Cem%3Edaal%3C%2Fem%3E.%20Instead%2C%20we%20have%20started%20eating%20wheat%20in%20the%20form%20of%20%3Cem%3Edaliya%20%3C%2Fem%3Eand%20%3Cem%3Ebaati.%20%3C%2Fem%3EAlso%2C%20we%20roast%20and%20add%20cumin%20and%20coriander%20to%20make%20the%20lentil%20taste%20better%2C%E2%80%9D%20she%20adds.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%E2%80%9CIt%E2%80%99s%20just%20simplified%20food%20choices%20for%20us%20now.%20The%20taste%20has%20now%20become%20secondary%20for%20us.%20However%2C%20we%20personally%20find%20the%20taste%20to%20be%20slightly%20better%20as%20the%20food%20is%20cooked%20slowly%20and%20the%20taste%20of%20the%20vegetable%20is%20retained%2C%E2%80%9D%20she%20says.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3ETalking%20about%20the%20limitation%20of%20the%20set%20up%2C%20Reva%20says%2C%20%E2%80%9CWhile%20we%20do%20most%20of%20the%20cooking%20in%20the%20solar%20cookers%2C%20we%20have%20also%20kept%20firewood%20%3Cem%3Echulha%20%3C%2Fem%3E(stove)%20as%20a%20backup%20for%20cloudy%20and%20rainy%20days.%20We%20collect%20firewood%20from%20trees%20around%20our%20house%20and%20also%20use%20coconut%20shells%20and%20cow%20dung%20cakes%20as%20fuel.%20We%20use%20firewood%20%3Cem%3Echulha%20%3C%2Fem%3Eonly%20once%20or%20twice%20a%20month.%E2%80%9D%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EAnother%20backup%20for%20cooking%20that%20they%20use%20during%20cloudy%20days%20and%20at%20night%20is%20their%20stored%20solar%20energy.%20Their%20house%20has%20a%20small%20850%20VA%20solar%20inverter%20that%20delivers%20enough%20charge%20for%20low-wattage%20electrical%20appliances.%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EShe%20fondly%20talks%20about%20how%20she%20repurposed%20and%20converted%20an%20old%20box-type%20solar%20cooker%20into%20a%20food%20dehydrator.%20They%20use%20it%20to%20dehydrate%20and%20preserve%20excess%20fruits%20when%20they%20have%20a%20bounty.%20The%20contraption%20